<ns2155:section xmlns:ns2155="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.technologies.java.j2ee.ejb.enterpriseBeans.sessionBeans.stateless.deploymentDescriptor.deploymentDescriptor">

  <ns2156:title xmlns:ns2156="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Writing the deployment descriptor</ns2156:title>
  <ns2157:para xmlns:ns2157="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"> 
    The deployment descriptor is an XML file describing the EJBs deployed within a single jar
    file. It describes for each bean the bean type (in our case it is a stateless session bean), the
    name and class of the bean as well as the home and remote interfaces. Potentially it also
    includes information for transaction and security handling. 
  </ns2157:para>
  <ns2158:para xmlns:ns2158="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"> 
    The XML file must be names <ns2159:literal xmlns:ns2159="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">ejb-jar.xml</ns2159:literal> and must be saved in a directory,
    <ns2160:literal xmlns:ns2160="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">META-INF</ns2160:literal>. 
    This directory contains the meta-information for the deployed bean(s). 
  </ns2158:para>
  
